-- pg_turbovec v1.23.0 -- Phase G-2a: WITH (graph = true), a new
-- Vamana-style navigable-graph index kind aiming to match HNSW's
-- query latency while keeping TurboQuant's storage compression.
--
-- This file is a *reference mirror*. The authoritative install
-- script is generated by `cargo pgrx schema`.
--
-- Wire format bumped to VERSION 6, ADDITIVE per kind (following the
-- same pattern as v5's KIND_COLBERT addition): a v4 single-vector
-- index and a v5 ColBERT index remain byte-identical under the v6
-- binary -- verified by dedicated tests
-- (v4_single_vector_bytes_unaffected_by_v6_binary,
-- decodes_v5_colbert_meta_unaffected_under_v6). NO REINDEX needed
-- for any existing v4/v5 index.
--
-- A graph index is a genuinely new on-disk shape (a Vamana adjacency
-- chain + entry-point slot id) that only a v6 binary produces --
-- there is no in-place migration of an existing flat/IVF/ColBERT
-- index into a graph index; build one explicitly with
-- `CREATE INDEX ... USING turbovec (col vec_*_ops) WITH (graph = true)`.
--
-- Scope (Phase G-2a, correctness-first): build + scan work end to
-- end with real recall (verified against exact linear scan on test
-- corpora). NOT yet done: VACUUM/tombstone integration (a graph
-- index currently rejects ambulkdelete with a clear ERROR rather
-- than silently corrupting the graph -- see
-- 's G-2b), aminsert (also
-- rejected with a clear ERROR -- rebuild the index after bulk
-- loading, same operational model IVF's build-then-query workflow
-- already uses), SIMD-optimized traversal (G-2c, scalar distance
-- computation only in this release), and the real 5M-scale
-- HNSW-latency gate measurement (G-2d, needs a cloud VM -- NOT yet run,
-- so no latency/recall claim vs HNSW is made by this release; see
--  for the gate this feature is ultimately
-- measured against before it can be called production-ready).
--
-- turbovec.probes / turbovec.search_k / IVF's lists reloption are
-- unaffected. `WITH (graph = true)` and `WITH (lists = N)` are
-- mutually exclusive on the same index (enforced in amoptions).
--
-- Migration: `ALTER EXTENSION pg_turbovec UPDATE TO '1.23.0';`.
-- No REINDEX for existing indexes.
